Doing ajax without jQuery is also good fun<p><pre><code>    var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();
    xhr.onreadystatechange = function() {
        if (xhr.readyState === 4) {
            callback(JSON.parse(xhr.responseText));
        }
    };
    xhr.open(&#x27;POST&#x27;, url, true);
    xhr.setRequestHeader(&#x27;Content-Type&#x27;, &#x27;application/json&#x27;);
    xhr.send(JSON.stringify(data));
</code></pre>
And that&#x27;s not taking care of errors, edge cases or Internet Explorer <i>at all</i>.<p>In jQuery:<p><pre><code>    $.post(url, data)</code></pre>
